gomodel:SYNGO_4189  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper uses cultured rat neurons and immunofluorescence antibody staining for endogenous synaptic proteins, and Figure 4 shows strong colocalization of Cntnap2/Caspr2 with the inhibitory presynaptic marker GAD65 and relatively weak colocalization of Cntnap2 with the excitatory presynaptic marker vGluT1.\n\nDescription in the figure legend.\nFIGURE 4\nDistribution of Caspr2 at pre-synaptic sites of excitatory and inhibitory axons. Confocal images of hippocampal neurons at DIV14 (A,B) or DIV21 (C) that were surface labeled for Caspr2 using LE1 IgGs (red). Cells were fixed and permeabilized before double-staining for MAP2 (blue), vGLUT1 (A, green) or GAD65 (B,C, green). (A') Enlarged areas shows glutamatergic pre-synaptic sites stained for Caspr2. (B',C'-C\"') Inhibitory pre-synaptic sites labeled for GAD65 (arrowheads) were intensely stained for Caspr2 at the contact with the soma (C\") or dendrites (B',C\"'). Note that GAD65-positive axons surrounding the soma of pyramidal neurons were heavily stained for Caspr2 (yellow arrows). (C') This enlarged area shows Caspr2 punctate immunostaining along a GAD65-positive axon apposed to a dendrite.\n\n20/01/2021 Dnyanada:\n1) The paper shows that Caspr2 colocalises with presynaptic inhibitory marker GAD65. The term \"..presynaptic membrane\" was chosen based on Figure 5 that shows that Caspr2 and GAD65 puncta lie in opposition of postsynaptic inhibitory synapse marker Gephyrin-GFP.\n2) The term \"integral component...\" was chosen based on additional literature indicating a membrane localisation of the protein as well as on the transmembrane topology of the Uniprot entry: CNTP2_MOUSE (Q9CPW0).. Experimental description: Materials and Methods (Cell culture section).\n\"Primary hippocampal cell cultures were performed from embryonic day 18-Wistar rats.\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
